===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[nædl]]''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[long]], [[thin]], sharp [[implement]] usually for [[piercing]] such as [[sew]]ing, or [[knit]]ting, [[acupuncture]], [[tattoo]]ing, [[body]] [[piercing]], [[medical]] [[injection]]s etc.
#: ''The seamstress threaded the '''needle''' to sew on a button.''
# A long, thin device for indicating [[measurement]]s on a [[dial]] or [[graph]], e.g. a ''compass needle''.
#: ''The '''needle''' on the fuel gauge pointed to empty.''
# A [[sensor]] for playing [[phonograph]] [[record]]s, a phonograph [[stylus]].
#: ''Ziggy bought some diamond '''needles''' for his hi-fi phonograph.''
# The long, pointed leaves of some [[conifers]].
#: ''I boiled some of the '''needles''' from the Christmas tree to add a pleasing scent to the air.''
# A [[weapon]] used in ancient China, and today by [[Shaolin]] monks.

